<meta content="TED Talk Subtitles and Transcript: Physician Gary Slutkin spent a decade fighting tuberculosis, cholera and AIDS epidemics in Africa. When he returned to the United States, he thought he&#39;d escape brutal epidemic deaths. But then he began to look more carefully at gun violence, noting that its spread followed the patterns of infectious diseases. A mind-flipping look at a problem that too many communities have accepted as a given. We&#39;ve reversed the impact of so many diseases, says Slutkin, and we can do the same with violence. (Filmed at TEDMED.)" name="description" />
